Title: My Life in Ruins
DateModified: '2019-02-03'
DatePublished: '2019-02-03'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/my-life-in-ruins
SetInCountry: Spain
Category: I didn't expect to find
AuthorName: Judith Singh
AuthorCountry: United States of America
Text: "After years of attempting to climb out of an abyss of physical and emotional\
  \ pain, on a whim, Jem renewed her Passport, booked a ticket, and traveled to Spain\
  \ to fulfill her once lifelong dream of hiking the Camino.  She had nothing left\
  \ to live for, nothing to lose, no one to whom she was beholden.  All was lost.\
  \  It was snowing in Philadelphia, and so grey; lifeless.  She was dead inside and\
  \ could barely find the energy to pack her dusty hiking gear and get to the airport.\
  \  Everything she had to do was exhausting.  Her therapist once told her she was\
  \ resilient.  Yet, Jem no longer believed this.  She had been tormented for so long,\
  \ there was no longer a spark inside, though she had found that spark time and time\
  \ again.  This time was different.  She was crushed.  All the former joys and loves\
  \ were gone.  How many times can you rebuild before you just stop trying?  \n\n\
  It was 2 PM in Madrid when the plane landed.  The air was ripe with the scent of\
  \ oranges.  It smelled ALIVE..."
